character_bio: First appearing in Street Fighter Alpha 3, Rainbow Mika is a pro wrestler who idolises Zangief. Many of her special moves are exaggerated versions of real-life wrestling techniques.
character_quote: I'll kick your ass! All right! Let's begiiiin!!!
character_motive_description: She is a Japanese professional wrestler from the Iwashigahama Japan Women's Pro-Wrestling organization.

character_bio: Preoccupied with paying off his son's debts, Marshall Law didn't realize how many of his students had quit his dojo until it was almost too late. With a large sum still to repay, Law was running out of ideas. As a last resort, he decided to search for a capable fighter to run the dojo. He asked his friend Paul if he knew anyone, and in his usual manner, Paul said he himself would be the perfect candidate. However, thinking that the dojo would go bust in half a day if Paul took control, Law politely refused. Instead, he put the word out that if any strong fighters wanted to try out for the job, they should come and prove their skills in combat. Challenger after challenger appeared, but none of them were good enough for Law. Then, one day, Law heard a rumor that a martial artist living in rural China was set to be the next God Fist master. Seeing this as his best chance yet, Law set off for his ancestral homeland.
character_quote: There's gotta be some way i can make some money off this!
character_motive_description: He enters the first King of Iron Fist Tournament in hopes of opening his own dojo with the winnings.

character_bio: Heir to the Masters family fortune, Ken is a flamoyant fighter who learned the art of Ansatsuken from Gouken. He also grew up alongside Ryu, a man he considers both his best friend and ultimate rival.
character_quote: Come on, let's turn up the heat.
character_motive_description: His goal is to test his power against many different fighters and strives to become stronger.

character_bio: The adopted son of Heihachi Mishima, raised to be a rival for Kazuya Mishima. After abandoning the Zaibatsu for various reasons, he ended up idling his time away in the Bahamas as manager of his own company… until a certain event disturbed his permanent vacation and entwined his fate with the Zaibatsu once again.
character_quote: Leave it to me. I won't disappoint.
character_motive_description: He is embroiled in a one-sided rivalry with his adoptive brother, Kazuya Mishima.

character_bio: Leo entered the King of Iron Fist Tournament in the hope of uncovering more about his deceased mother, who had been a researcher for the Mishima Zaibatsu. When Leo learned that his battle arena was to be a Zaibatsu-owned dojo, he couldn't believe his luck. However, when he got there, the dojo was in ruin. The moonlight poured in through holes in the walls and roof, illuminating the floor with an eerie beauty. A short while later, a strange, floating silhouette appeared, and slowly glided toward Leo. The silhouette held a sword in its left hand that rotated at a mind-bending speed. What the hell was this thing? It looked like some kind of a flying squid or octopus! Was it a demon…? Then it finally dawned on Leo: This bizarre creature was his opponent. Cautiously, he prepared to fight.
character_quote: Get ready!
character_motive_description: Leo seeks the truth about the murder of their mother.

character_bio: Once a fighter who had won the hearts of fans with his excellent sensibility and handsome good looks, he decided to transform himself completely by gaining weight to eliminate the perceived disadvantage he had in a fight due to his body type. His fans were disappointed, as on the outside it looked like he'd merely put on a few too many pounds, but Bob was definitely pleased with himself.
character_quote: Speed and weight!
character_motive_description: He entered the sixth tournament to silence his doubters.

character_bio: Introduced in Super Street Fighter IV, Juri is a sadistic Tae Kwon Do expert with a cybernetic eye. She loathes Shadaloo for killing her parents, and wants nothing more than to see M. Bison dead.
character_quote: Well then, where do you want me to break you first?
character_motive_description: She is a brutal South Korean Taekwondo martial artist who derives pleasure from inflicting pain on others.

character_quote: Let my beauty intoxicate you.
character_motive_description: He is a claw-wielding, narcissistic, Spanish ninja, obsessed with beauty and personal bodyguard to M. Bison.

character_bio: If you know anything about Street Fighter, chances are you've come across this all-American air force pilot and his flat-top haircut before. Guile returns in Street Fighter V seeking a comrade he previously believed dead.
character_quote: No need for talk. Let's do this!
character_motive_description: He is a major in the United States Air Force whose goal is to finish the criminal organization Shadaloo.

character_bio: After failing to apprehend Jin Kazama, Nina Williams decided it was time for her and the Mishima Zaibatsu to go their separate ways. On her first private assassination job, she was tasked with infiltrating a mafia wedding… posing as the bride! During the ceremony, a firefight broke out where Nina took out all her targets. However, the commotion had attracted the Tekken Force, who had been dispatched to suppress the violence, and they gave chase. With the Tekken Force in hot pursuit, Nina made her escape. That's when she bumped into a man she found vaguely familiar. The man wouldn't leave her alone. He seemed to have something he wanted to say to her… Nina decided that a confrontation was her best chance of escape.
character_quote: You've got a date with death.
character_motive_description: She was contracted to assassinate the current head of Mishima Zaibatsu.

character_bio: The leader of the Mishima Zaibatsu and the man who declared war on the world. Fighting the Devil inside him which gets stronger everyday, he yearns to be rid of it once and for all. When his battle is over at last, will he find hope… or despair?
character_quote: Power is everything.
character_motive_description: He wishes to avenge the apparent death of his mother Jun Kazama.

character_bio: First introduced in Street Fighter III: Second Impact, Urien is the vice president of the Illuminati. Unlike his benevolent brother, this self-serving tyrant is only interested in furthering his own interests.
character_quote: Don't worry. I'll end you quickly.
character_motive_description: He is a ruthless former disciple of the Illuminati.

character_bio: As an agent for the UN's intelligence bureau, Master Raven embarked on her latest top-secret mission: Infiltrate the King of Iron Fist Tournament and confront her assigned target. In the frozen area that was to be her battleground, Master Raven stood, arms folded, face to face with her subordinate's sworn enemy, who simply narrowed his eyes and took up a fighting pose.
character_quote: It's just business. Don't take it personally.
character_motive_description: She is an agent for the UN's intelligence bureau.

character_bio: Once a mindless doll under the control of Shadaloo, Cammy broke free of her brainwashing and joined a Special Forces unit called Delta Red. Her former codename was Killer Bee. She also has a fondness for cats.
character_quote: I fight for those I want to protect!
character_motive_description: She is an MI6 operative for the British government.

character_bio: Known as the Red Cyclone in his native Russia, Zangief is a living mountain of muscle who wrestles bears for fun. He first appeared in Street Fighter II with his signature spinning pile driver.
character_quote: My iron body is invincible! So beware!
character_motive_description: He is a national Russian hero who is always seen fighting for the glory of his country.

character_bio: Making her Street Fighter debut, Menat is the apprentice of a famous fortune-teller. She fights with a crystal sphere that she controls with her soul power.
character_quote: Have you considered your destiny? Do you believe in fate?
character_motive_description: She is the Soul Power wielding apprentice of Rose.

character_bio: If you know anything about Street Fighter, chances are you've come across this all-American air force pilot and his flat-top haircut before. Guile returns in Street Fighter V seeking a comrade he previously believed dead.
character_quote: No need for talk. Let's do this!
character_motive_description: He is a major in the United States Air Force whose goal is to finish the criminal organization Shadaloo.

character_bio: Preoccupied with paying off his son's debts, Marshall Law didn't realize how many of his students had quit his dojo until it was almost too late. With a large sum still to repay, Law was running out of ideas. As a last resort, he decided to search for a capable fighter to run the dojo. He asked his friend Paul if he knew anyone, and in his usual manner, Paul said he himself would be the perfect candidate. However, thinking that the dojo would go bust in half a day if Paul took control, Law politely refused. Instead, he put the word out that if any strong fighters wanted to try out for the job, they should come and prove their skills in combat. Challenger after challenger appeared, but none of them were good enough for Law. Then, one day, Law heard a rumor that a martial artist living in rural China was set to be the next God Fist master. Seeing this as his best chance yet, Law set off for his ancestral homeland.
character_quote: There's gotta be some way i can make some money off this!
character_motive_description: He enters the first King of Iron Fist Tournament in hopes of opening his own dojo with the winnings.

character_bio: Lili entered the King of Iron Fist Tournament again without telling her father this time either. There she was anyway, smiling as the rapturous crowd looked on and her opponent entered the arena. Lili was set to fight Asuka Kazama, someone she had personally considered her greatest rival for many years. If Lili saw the look of annoyance on Asuka's face, it didn't show; she just walked elegantly to the center of the ring like she owned it, all the while thanking Lady Luck for the opportunity to fight her rival.
character_quote: You surely don't believe… you can beat me?
character_motive_description: She clashes with her father over his dealings with devious Mishima Zaibatsu corporation.
ethnicity_description: I Like Very So Match This Task And Very Happy Thank You.
feedback: good. very enjoy this game survey

character_bio: As one of the two most outlandish characters introduced in Street Fighter II, Dhalsim is a yoga master who can breathe fire and stretch his limbs at will. He’s always been one of the series’ more senior characters, as evidenced by his new white beard.
character_quote: I am not very fond of conflict.
character_motive_description: He enters the tournament to raise money for his village, and continues to roam the world helping those in need.

feedback: good. very enjoy this game survey

character_bio: As the first lady of Street Fighter, Chun-Li is widely regarded as the strongest woman in the world. She’s an agent for Interpol and is hell-bent on bringing both M. Bison and Shadaloo to justice.
character_quote: I'll show you my Kung-Fu!
character_motive_description: She relentlessly seeks revenge for the death of her father at the hands of M. Bison.

feedback: good. very enjoy this game survey

character_bio: First appearing in Guy's ending for Street Fighter Alpha II, Zeku is the 38th successor of Bushinryu. Using a special ninja technique, he can reverse his aging to become young again.
character_quote: Lets party! If you think you can keep up.
character_motive_description: He was formerly a grandmaster but after being succeeded by his pupil, he set out on a journey of self-discovery.

character_bio: Written off as dead after the events of the Street Fighter Alpha series, Nash makes an unexpected return in Street Fighter V. His Frankenstein’s monster-esque appearance suggests he’s not the harbinger of justice we once knew…
character_quote: I'll show no mercy!
character_motive_description: He is a former Captain of the United States Air Force and friend of Guile.
ethnicity_description: I Like Very So Match This Task And Very Happy Thank You.
feedback: good. very enjoy this game survey

character_bio: The original leader of the Mishima Zaibatsu, and the fighter known as the 'King of the Iron Fist.' Heihachi continues to fight for control of the Mishima Zaibatsu against his son, Kazuya, and his grandson, Jin. After having recovered from the injuries he sustained in the suicide attack on him from the G Corporation's Jack units, Heihachi is back with an iron fist--and body to match.
character_quote: You fool! I am invincible!
character_motive_description: He is the leader of an empire known as the Mishima Zaibatsu.

character_bio: Introduced in Super Street Fighter IV, Juri is a sadistic Tae Kwon Do expert with a cybernetic eye. She loathes Shadaloo for killing her parents, and wants nothing more than to see M. Bison dead.
character_quote: Well then, where do you want me to break you first?
character_motive_description: She is a brutal South Korean Taekwondo martial artist who derives pleasure from inflicting pain on others.

character_bio: As one of the four kings of Shadaloo, Balrog is a remorseless boxer who loves money, women, and bourbon. As long as Shadaloo continue to provide him with all three, he will fight for them.
character_quote: There's no escape!
character_motive_description: He is a greedy American boxer and personal bodyguard to M. Bison.

character_bio: Ling Xiaoyu infiltrated the Mishima Zaibatsu building in search of information relating to Jin Kazama's disappearance. Creeping deeper into the enemy territory under the guards' noses, she eventually hears Heihachi Mishima's voice coming from a room; he was giving orders about locating Jin. Just as Xiaoyu was about to sneak into the room, a man dressed all in white emerged and pushed her back. 'Take me to Jin!' Xiaoyu demanded, unflinching. The man stood there for a moment, before ordering Xiaoyu to follow him. He led her to the roof, then silently turned toward her, and readied himself to fight. Xiaoyu took up her fighting stance, and said, 'So that's how it is... If you think I'm just some little girl, you're sadly mistaken.'
character_quote: I'm going to stop Jin!
character_motive_description: She is a sixteen-year-old Chinese martial artist.

character_bio: Kazumi Mishima, wife of Heihachi Mishima, is well versed in Hachijyo Karate. She was childhood friends with her husband Heihachi and eventually they fell in love. Through their love they birthed a healthy young boy. Fast forward a few years later, Heihachi would become the head of a huge organization called the Mishima Zaibatsu, with plans to conquer the world. Kazumi loved Heihachi unconditionally, but at the same time he was beginning to feel dangerous. In this state, Heihachi threw the world into a war and Kazumi took it upon herself to stop him.
character_quote: I will teach you the meaning of fear.
character_motive_description: She married to Heihachi because her clan foresaw his attempted world domination in the future and sent her to kill him.

character_bio: First appearing in Street Fighter III as a non-playable character, Kolin is a member of the secret Illuminati organization. Gill gifted her the power of ice and she's been loyal to him ever since.
character_quote: It's so nice to meet.
character_motive_description: She is a conniving and devoted agent of the Illuminati.

character_bio: A former officer of the Mishima Zaibatsu's special military unit, the Tekken Force, Lars enacted a coup d'état and rebelled against his former employer. Lars continues to fight despite the loss of his fallen comrades, and his bloody rebellion is nowhere near finished.
character_quote: Think you can stop me?
character_motive_description: He is a member of the Tekken Force paramilitary unit, confronting the corrupt Mishima Zaibatsu corporation.

character_bio: King is not only a masked professional wrestler, but also the proud owner of an orphanage. Recently, King's sworn friend and comrade, Craig Marduk, as well as the man King called his master, both engaged in a bloody fight which left them with critical injuries. King desperately wanted to come to his friends' rescue, but knew that their operations wouldn't come cheap. At the same time, King's orphanage was in constant danger owing to the war that raged between G Corporation and the Mishima Zaibatsu. Finding himself caught between a rock and a hard place, King entered the King of Iron Fist Tournament with his eyes set firmly on the cash prize.
character_quote: Let's do this.
character_motive_description: He is a Catholic priest who became a masked wrestler in order to support an orphanage.

character_bio: Feng Wei had always abided by what was written on the God Fist scroll: 'Defeat all other masters and conquer their styles; the perfect warrior transcends all to become the Dragon God.' Having fought masters of many different styles, Feng returned to his childhood training ground to continue his intense training regime. Then one day, an unexpected visitor appeared before Feng: a mysterious man who exuded strength. When the man made it clear that his desire was to fight, Feng had no reason to refuse. He accepted his opponent's challenge in silence, and prepared to battle.
character_quote: Come on!
character_motive_description: He seeks the secrets of the God Fist scrolls that were stolen by the Mishima family.
feedback: No, all the instructions were very clear. Thank you.

character_bio: Steve Fox has had plenty of run-ins with the Mishima Zaibatsu, but he never gave up his search for information about his past. Though his mother's identity remained a mystery, one name in particular began to crop up time and again: Nina Williams. Believing she knew something, Steve began investigating her whereabouts until he came up with a promising lead. The information led him to an imposing cathedral. As he considered how best to proceed, a figure appeared from inside, dressed in a tattered wedding gown. It was Nina, who seemed to be running away from something. Steve told her to stop, but she ignored him and fled. Determined not to let this opportunity escape him, he blocked her path.
character_quote: Hey you… You wanna try me?
character_motive_description: He fights to escape the mafia and find his mother.
feedback: No, all the instructions were very clear. Thank you.

character_bio: Daughter of the Kazama Traditional Martial Arts School and known as 'Gang Mediator' in her hometown. Ever since she involved herself in a certain street fight, Lili has viewed her as a rival. She knows that Jin Kazama is her cousin and vows to take him down.
character_quote: When you resort to fighting, everyone loses.
character_motive_description: She believes very strongly in justice and devotes much of her free time to being a "pacifist" vigilante who is breaking up fights.

character_bio: As a top contender for the wealthiest fighter in the Street Fighter universe, Karin Kanzuki is understandably snobbish. She also counts the likes of Sakura, Ken and R. Mika among her rivals.
character_quote: I'll show you the divide in our class!
character_motive_description: Her father is a rather strict man as he constantly pushes his daughter into becoming a better heir to the Kanzuki family fortune, as he wanted a son.

The most powerful exorcist of the current generation is Claudio, who was visiting the Mishima Zaibatsu as their groups join forces to subdue a certain evil. After sharing information on the targets, Kazuya Mishima and Jin Kazama, Claudio left the control room only to be confronted by a young girl. He was about to call the guards when she demanded to be taken to Jin. A plan sprung to Claudio's mind. He led her to the roof, and with a grin prepared to face her in combat.
character_quote: This is no place for amateurs.

character_motive_description: His goal is to test his power against many different fighters and strives to become stronger.

character_bio: Josie Rizal tried her best to support her family by balancing two jobs. One as a model, and one as a professional kickboxer. One day, while she was out running on her usual training course along the mountain roads, she was suddenly confronted by an enormous, hairy creature! Josie screamed, and then fled half in tears, but the creature remained hot on her heels. Realizing she had little chance of escape, Josie abruptly came to a halt, then turned trembling, to face her feral foe…
character_quote: I got this!
character_motive_description: She reluctantly agrees to her parents expectations and train Kickboxing.

character_bio: As an agent for the UN's intelligence bureau, Master Raven embarked on her latest top-secret mission: Infiltrate the King of Iron Fist Tournament and confront her assigned target. character_bio: Leo entered the King of Iron Fist Tournament in the hope of uncovering more about his deceased mother, who had been a researcher for the Mishima Zaibatsu. When Leo learned that his battle arena was to be a Zaibatsu-owned dojo, he couldn't believe his luck. However, when he got there, the dojo was in ruin. The moonlight poured in through holes in the walls and roof, illuminating the floor with an eerie beauty. A short while later, a strange, floating silhouette appeared, and slowly glided toward Leo. The silhouette held a sword in its left hand that rotated at a mind-bending speed. What the hell was this thing? It looked like some kind of a flying squid or octopus! Was it a demon…? Then it finally dawned on Leo: This bizarre creature was his opponent. Cautiously, he prepared to fight.
character_quote: Get ready!
character_motive_description: Leo seeks the truth about the murder of their mother.

character_bio: Kazuya was raised as the heir to the Mishima Zaibatsu, but rebelled against his father Heihachi. After awakening the power of the devil within him, he's finally able to control it.
character_quote: It's time for you to meet your end!
character_motive_description: He seeks to take revenge against his father for having thrown him down a cliff years prior.

character_bio: First appearing in Street Fighter Alpha 3, Rainbow Mika is a pro wrestler who idolises Zangief. Many of her special moves are exaggerated versions of real-life wrestling techniques.
character_quote: I'll kick your ass! All right! Let's begiiiin!!!
character_motive_description: She is a Japanese professional wrestler from the Iwashigahama Japan Women's Pro-Wrestling organization.

character_bio: Lucky Chloe is a pop sensation, and the face of the G Corporation brand. When a mysterious man burst into G Corp and took out guard after guard with dance-like techniques, Lucky Chloe fearlessly walked right up to him and blocked his path. She threw the man one of her trademark smiles and issued him a challenge: Fight her, and if he loses he'll have to work as her backup dancer! Without caring if he'd accepted the conditions or not, she prepared for battle.
character_quote: Are you ready?
character_motive_description: She is hired by G Corporation to be a mascot commercial

character_bio: Rounding off the quartet of new combatants in Street Fighter V is F.A.N.G. This assassin works for Shadaloo as M. Bison’s second in command.
character_quote: Two minutes! I'll finish you in two minutes!
character_motive_description: He is the second-in-command of Shadaloo, ranking only below M. Bison in the hierarchy.

character_bio: Kazumi Mishima, wife of Heihachi Mishima, is well versed in Hachijyo Karate. She was childhood friends with her husband Heihachi and eventually they fell in love. Through their love they birthed a healthy young boy. Fast forward a few years later, Heihachi would become the head of a huge organization called the Mishima Zaibatsu, with plans to conquer the world. Kazumi loved Heihachi unconditionally, but at the same time he was beginning to feel dangerous. In this state, Heihachi threw the world into a war and Kazumi took it upon herself to stop him.
character_quote: I will teach you the meaning of fear.
character_motive_description: She married to Heihachi because her clan foresaw his attempted world domination in the future and sent her to kill him.

character_bio: If there’s one character in the Street Fighter universe that can be described as pure evil, it has to be M. Bison. Brainwashing, human experimentation and remorseless murder, there’s nothing this dictator won’t do to fulfil his ambitions.
character_quote: Bow down before my Psycho Power!
character_motive_description: He is a self-imposed dictator and megalomaniac seeking world domination.

character_bio: Much like Dee Jay before him, Rashid is an enthusiastic fighter who's rarely seen without a smile on his face. He's also something of a gadget lover, as can be seen by the tornado-firing rucksack he carries on his back.
character_quote: I'm Rashid of the turbulent wind. Remember the name well.
character_motive_description: Rashid is travelling the world in search of a missing friend who has been kidnapped by Shadaloo.

character_bio: As one of the two most outlandish characters introduced in Street Fighter II, Dhalsim is a yoga master who can breathe fire and stretch his limbs at will. He’s always been one of the series’ more senior characters, as evidenced by his new white beard.
character_quote: I am not very fond of conflict.
character_motive_description: He enters the tournament to raise money for his village, and continues to roam the world helping those in need.

character_bio: Katarina Alves lost both her parents at a young age, and spent several years at an orphanage before being adopted by a man she'd never met. Initially, Katarina rebelled against him using a whole manner of profane language, but the man's kindness and patience eventually wore her hard exterior down. In time, they grew close, though her penchant for profane language remained. One day, Katarina's adoptive father vanished. As much as she wanted to find him, she lacked the money to do so. But then she learned of the King of Iron Fist Tournament. The savage techniques the man had taught her gave Katarina hope that she could win and take the cash prize. The day of the first match arrived, and the arena was none other than the roof of G Corporation's Millennium Tower. When Katarina first laid eyes on her opponent, all she saw was an enormous hulk of muscle. There was no way he could be human…
character_quote: Sorry, but you're gonna have to die.
character_motive_description: She is currently searching for her missing adoptive father.

character_bio: Once a mindless doll under the control of Shadaloo, Cammy broke free of her brainwashing and joined a Special Forces unit called Delta Red. Her former codename was Killer Bee. She also has a fondness for cats.
character_quote: I fight for those I want to protect!
character_motive_description: She is an MI6 operative for the British government.

character_bio: When Paul Phoenix, the golden boy of the martial arts world, steps into the ring, the excitement in the crowd is palpable. But this time when his opponent's name rang over the arena's loudspeakers, he could only scratch his head in disbelief. It was Kuma… again! However, Kuma was nowhere to be seen. Word went round that the bear had dropped out of the tournament. The ring announcer informed the spectators of a last-minute change to the fight card. Relieved, Paul awaits the entrance of his long-anticipated human opponent…
character_quote: I'll show you the power of the strongest in the universe… but not for free!
character_motive_description: He fights in hopes of winning the prize money and to prove he is the world's best fighter.

character_bio: Rounding off the quartet of new combatants in Street Fighter V is F.A.N.G. This assassin works for Shadaloo as M. Bison’s second in command.

character_bio: Ling Xiaoyu infiltrated the Mishima Zaibatsu building in search of information relating to Jin Kazama's disappearance. Creeping deeper into the enemy territory under the guards' noses, she eventually hears Heihachi Mishima's voice coming from a room; he was giving orders about locating Jin. Just as Xiaoyu was about to sneak into the room, a man dressed all in white emerged and pushed her back. 'Take me to Jin!' Xiaoyu demanded, unflinching. The man stood there for a moment, before ordering Xiaoyu to follow him. He led her to the roof, then silently turned toward her, and readied himself to fight. Xiaoyu took up her fighting stance, and said, 'So that's how it is... If you think I'm just some little girl, you're sadly mistaken.'
character_quote: I'm going to stop Jin!
character_motive_description: She is a sixteen-year-old Chinese martial artist.
feedback: I felt like some characters have exaggerated features but are also designed realistically so answering those questions made me feel like my answers were contradictory.

character_bio: Once a fighter who had won the hearts of fans with his excellent sensibility and handsome good looks, he decided to transform himself completely by gaining weight to eliminate the perceived disadvantage he had in a fight due to his body type. character_bio: Josie Rizal tried her best to support her family by balancing two jobs. One as a model, and one as a professional kickboxer. One day, while she was out running on her usual training course along the mountain roads, she was suddenly confronted by an enormous, hairy creature! Josie screamed, and then fled half in tears, but the creature remained hot on her heels. Realizing she had little chance of escape, Josie abruptly came to a halt, then turned trembling, to face her feral foe…
character_quote: I got this!
character_motive_description: She reluctantly agrees to her parents expectations and train Kickboxing.

character_quote: Okay. Let's rumble.
character_motive_description: He enters the third World Warrior tournament after its sponsor, Gill, seriously injures his best friend and father figure Tom.

In the frozen area that was to be her battleground, Master Raven stood, arms folded, face to face with her subordinate's sworn enemy, who simply narrowed his eyes and took up a fighting pose.
character_quote: It's just business. Don't take it personally.
character_motive_description: She is an agent for the UN's intelligence bureau.

character_bio: After he defeated Azazel, Jin Kazama was apprehended by UN troops. As his unconscious body was being transported by helicopter, he became possessed by his devil form, ripped free from his straitjacket, tore through the helicopter's fuselage with a powerful beam attack, and then escaped. Intermittently fending off the UN's attempts to recapture him, Devil Jin wandered the desert until he stumbled across a town in the Middle East. His arrival at the town's bazaar sent the civilians fleeing for their lives, turning the once buzzing settlement into an abandoned husk. That is until a certain someone showed his face…
character_quote: Fear my wrath.
character_motive_description: He seeks to achieve ultimate power and will do whatever it takes to achieve it.

character_bio: Laura is a brand-new Street Fighter character and a practitioner of Matsuda jiu-jitsu. If you recognize the name Matsuda, it's because Laura is the elder sister of Sean from Street Fighter III.
character_quote: Boom! That's how to start a fight and finish it quickly!
character_motive_description: She has a desire to promote her family's fighting style.

character_bio: Shaheen works for a private military firm specializing in the provision of security services. During his time in the army, he earned a reputation as an expert in one-on-one combat. One day, his friend and owner of a company involved in the oil industry died suddenly under mysterious circumstances. In the postmortem the death was listed as accidental, but Shaheen suspected foul play when his friend's company was suddenly bought by G Corporation and the management, all family members, resigned. He began to investigate the matter, and a relative of a close friend confided in him that a demonic man was pulling the strings at G Corp: Kazuya Mishima. Shaheen struggled to believe a real demon could exist, but his investigations revealed that Kazuya could be worse than any of hell's creations. Shaheen was torn: Should he take revenge for his friend's death by destroying that demon, or not? Wracked with doubt, he embarked on a solo mission to infiltrate G Corp.
character_quote: I do not wish to hurt you, but I will fight if I must.
character_motive_description: He is a bodyguard for a Private Military Company, who is tasked in protecting key figures in the world.
feedback: great survey! A lot of fun and great pay.

character_bio: The original leader of the Mishima Zaibatsu, and the fighter known as the 'King of the Iron Fist.' Heihachi continues to fight for control of the Mishima Zaibatsu against his son, Kazuya, and his grandson, Jin. After having recovered from the injuries he sustained in the suicide attack on him from the G Corporation's Jack units, Heihachi is back with an iron fist--and body to match.
character_quote: You fool! I am invincible!
character_motive_description: He is the leader of an empire known as the Mishima Zaibatsu.
feedback: great survey! A lot of fun and great pay.

character_bio: Heir to the Masters family fortune, Ken is a flamoyant fighter who learned the art of Ansatsuken from Gouken. He also grew up alongside Ryu, a man he considers both his best friend and ultimate rival.
character_quote: Come on, let's turn up the heat.
character_motive_description: His goal is to test his power against many different fighters and strives to become stronger.

character_motive_description: He is a national Russian hero who is always seen fighting for the glory of his country.

character_bio: As a top contender for the wealthiest fighter in the Street Fighter universe, Karin Kanzuki is understandably snobbish. She also counts the likes of Sakura, Ken and R. Mika among her rivals.
character_quote: I'll show you the divide in our class!
character_motive_description: Her father is a rather strict man as he constantly pushes his daughter into becoming a better heir to the Kanzuki family fortune, as he wanted a son.

character_bio: Feng Wei had always abided by what was written on the God Fist scroll: 'Defeat all other masters and conquer their styles; the perfect warrior transcends all to become the Dragon God.' Having fought masters of many different styles, Feng returned to his childhood training ground to continue his intense training regime. Then one day, an unexpected visitor appeared before Feng: a mysterious man who exuded strength. When the man made it clear that his desire was to fight, Feng had no reason to refuse. He accepted his opponent's challenge in silence, and prepared to battle.
character_quote: Come on!
character_motive_description: He seeks the secrets of the God Fist scrolls that were stolen by the Mishima family.

character_bio: King is not only a masked professional wrestler, but also the proud owner of an orphanage. Recently, King's sworn friend and comrade, Craig Marduk, as well as the man King called his master, both engaged in a bloody fight which left them with critical injuries. King desperately wanted to come to his friends' rescue, but knew that their operations wouldn't come cheap. At the same time, King's orphanage was in constant danger owing to the war that raged between G Corporation and the Mishima Zaibatsu. Finding himself caught between a rock and a hard place, King entered the King of Iron Fist Tournament with his eyes set firmly on the cash prize.
character_quote: Let's do this.
character_motive_description: He is a Catholic priest who became a masked wrestler in order to support an orphanage.

character_bio: A mysterious fighter… a demon. He finds himself in the middle of the Mishima blood feud by a pre-existing relationship with Kazumi, Hehiachi's wife. He makes his debut in TEKKEN 7 promising to fulfill a debt owed to Kazumi.
character_quote: Can you withstand my power?
character_motive_description: He seeks to repay a debt to Kazumi Mishima for saving his life from an unknown critical situation.

character_bio: As one of the four new characters introduced in Street Fighter V, much of Necalli’s past is shrouded in mystery. His fighting style is best described as animalistic, due to his feral slashes and stomps.
character_quote: Devour-our-our…
character_motive_description: He is an ancient, mysterious entity searching for souls of powerful fighters to devour.

character_bio: After losing his sister in an airstrike ordered by the Mishima Zaibatsu under the direction of Jin Kazama, Miguel Caballero Rojo devoted his life to seeking revenge. However, when Jin suddenly vanishes without a trace, Miguel's life purpose disappears along with him. From that point forward, Miguel began to wander like a specter from battle-torn town to battle-torn town. One day, as he ambled through rows of dilapidated buildings, he stumbled across a strangely familiar hooded man. There in front of him was none other than his sworn enemy, Jin. Consumed by both euphoria and rage, Miguel becomes frenzied and goes in for the kill.
character_quote: You look like you're ready to lose.
character_motive_description: He fights to avenge his sister who is killed on her wedding day by Mishima Zaibatsu fighter jets.

character_bio: As the first lady of Street Fighter, Chun-Li is widely regarded as the strongest woman in the world. She’s an agent for Interpol and is hell-bent on bringing both M. Bison and Shadaloo to justice.
character_quote: I'll show you my Kung-Fu!
character_motive_description: She relentlessly seeks revenge for the death of her father at the hands of M. Bison.

character_bio: Leo entered the King of Iron Fist Tournament in the hope of uncovering more about his deceased mother, who had been a researcher for the Mishima Zaibatsu. When Leo learned that his battle arena was to be a Zaibatsu-owned dojo, he couldn't believe his luck. However, when he got there, the dojo was in ruin. The moonlight poured in through holes in the walls and roof, illuminating the floor with an eerie beauty. A short while later, a strange, floating silhouette appeared, and slowly glided toward Leo. The silhouette held a sword in its left hand that rotated at a mind-bending speed. What the hell was this thing? It looked like some kind of a flying squid or octopus! Was it a demon…? Then it finally dawned on Leo: This bizarre creature was his opponent. Cautiously, he prepared to fight.
character_quote: Get ready!
character_motive_description: Leo seeks the truth about the murder of their mother.

character_bio: Preoccupied with paying off his son's debts, Marshall Law didn't realize how many of his students had quit his dojo until it was almost too late. With a large sum still to repay, Law was running out of ideas. As a last resort, he decided to search for a capable fighter to run the dojo. He asked his friend Paul if he knew anyone, and in his usual manner, Paul said he himself would be the perfect candidate. However, thinking that the dojo would go bust in half a day if Paul took control, Law politely refused. Instead, he put the word out that if any strong fighters wanted to try out for the job, they should come and prove their skills in combat. Challenger after challenger appeared, but none of them were good enough for Law. Then, one day, Law heard a rumor that a martial artist living in rural China was set to be the next God Fist master. Seeing this as his best chance yet, Law set off for his ancestral homeland.
character_quote: There's gotta be some way i can make some money off this!
character_motive_description: He enters the first King of Iron Fist Tournament in hopes of opening his own dojo with the winnings.

character_motive_description: He is a claw-wielding, narcissistic, Spanish ninja, obsessed with beauty and personal bodyguard to M. Bison.

character_motive_description: She was created to protect Jin Kazama and serves him through her travels.

character_bio: Sergei Dragunov entered the King of Iron Fist Tournament on army orders. At the designated arena of his first match, a woman appeared before him. There was something strangely familiar about her… It didn't take Dragunov long to figure out who she was, and he wasted no time in readying himself for combat.
character_motive_description: He is a Russian Spetsnaz soldier.
feedback: yes,i feel this game type is very interesting and challenging.

character_bio: As one of the four new characters introduced in Street Fighter V, much of Necalli’s past is shrouded in mystery. His fighting style is best described as animalistic, due to his feral slashes and stomps.
character_quote: Devour-our-our…
character_motive_description: He is an ancient, mysterious entity searching for souls of powerful fighters to devour.
feedback: yes,i feel this game type is very interesting and challenging.

character_bio: Steve Fox has had plenty of run-ins with the Mishima Zaibatsu, but he never gave up his search for information about his past. Though his mother's identity remained a mystery, one name in particular began to crop up time and again: Nina Williams. Believing she knew something, Steve began investigating her whereabouts until he came up with a promising lead. The information led him to an imposing cathedral. As he considered how best to proceed, a figure appeared from inside, dressed in a tattered wedding gown. It was Nina, who seemed to be running away from something. Steve told her to stop, but she ignored him and fled. Determined not to let this opportunity escape him, he blocked her path.
character_quote: Hey you… You wanna try me?
character_motive_description: He fights to escape the mafia and find his mother.

character_bio: As one of the four kings of Shadaloo, Balrog is a remorseless boxer who loves money, women, and bourbon. As long as Shadaloo continue to provide him with all three, he will fight for them.
character_quote: There's no escape!
character_motive_description: He is a greedy American boxer and personal bodyguard to M. Bison.

character_bio: Shaheen works for a private military firm specializing in the provision of security services. During his time in the army, he earned a reputation as an expert in one-on-one combat. One day, his friend and owner of a company involved in the oil industry died suddenly under mysterious circumstances. In the postmortem the death was listed as accidental, but Shaheen suspected foul play when his friend's company was suddenly bought by G Corporation and the management, all family members, resigned. He began to investigate the matter, and a relative of a close friend confided in him that a demonic man was pulling the strings at G Corp: Kazuya Mishima. Shaheen struggled to believe a real demon could exist, but his investigations revealed that Kazuya could be worse than any of hell's creations. Shaheen was torn: Should he take revenge for his friend's death by destroying that demon, or not? Wracked with doubt, he embarked on a solo mission to infiltrate G Corp.
character_quote: I do not wish to hurt you, but I will fight if I must.
character_motive_description: He is a bodyguard for a Private Military Company, who is tasked in protecting key figures in the world.

character_bio: An android created by Dr. Bosconovitch as a bodyguard for Jin Kazama. Her design itself is modeled after Bosconovitch's own lost daughter. Her fighting capabilities are extremely high. She can perform attacks with high mobility using arm-mounted missiles and thrusters.
character_quote: I am Alisa, nice to meet you
character_motive_description: She was created to protect Jin Kazama and serves him through her travels.

character_bio: Written off as dead after the events of the Street Fighter Alpha series, Nash makes an unexpected return in Street Fighter V. His Frankenstein’s monster-esque appearance suggests he’s not the harbinger of justice we once knew…
character_quote: I'll show no mercy!
character_motive_description: He is a former Captain of the United States Air Force and friend of Guile.

character_bio: The original leader of the Mishima Zaibatsu, and the fighter known as the 'King of the Iron Fist.' Heihachi continues to fight for control of the Mishima Zaibatsu against his son, Kazuya, and his grandson, Jin. After having recovered from the injuries he sustained in the suicide attack on him from the G Corporation's Jack units, Heihachi is back with an iron fist--and body to match.
character_quote: You fool! I am invincible!
character_motive_description: He is the leader of an empire known as the Mishima Zaibatsu.

character_bio: Hwoarang sees one man as his rival: Jin Kazama. Jin, CEO of the Mishima Zaibatsu, declared war against the world, and in the ensuing turmoil vanished suddenly, without a trace. Suspecting there is more to Jin's disappearance than meets the eye, Hwoarang vowed to track him down. With only a shred of reliable information at hand, he headed to the Middle East. After a series of dead leads, Hwoarang heard word that a demon had appeared in a town. Without a second thought, he got on his motorcycle and hammered down there. When he arrived, the place had been deserted, save for Jin Kazama in his devil form.
character_quote: Come at me! I'll take you down.
character_motive_description: He is the Taekwondo student of Baek Doo San, and entered the third Tournament to get revenge for his master.

character_bio: As an agent for the UN's intelligence bureau, Master Raven embarked on her latest top-secret mission: Infiltrate the King of Iron Fist Tournament and confront her assigned target. In the frozen area that was to be her battleground, Master Raven stood, arms folded, face to face with her subordinate's sworn enemy, who simply narrowed his eyes and took up a fighting pose.
character_quote: It's just business. Don't take it personally.
character_motive_description: She is an agent for the UN's intelligence bureau.

character_bio: Sergei Dragunov entered the King of Iron Fist Tournament on army orders. At the designated arena of his first match, a woman appeared before him. There was something strangely familiar about her… It didn't take Dragunov long to figure out who she was, and he wasted no time in readying himself for combat.
character_motive_description: He is a Russian Spetsnaz soldier.

character_quote: I'll show no mercy!
character_motive_description: He is a former Captain of the United States Air Force and friend of Guile.

character_bio: If there’s one character in the Street Fighter universe that can be described as pure evil, it has to be M. Bison. Brainwashing, human experimentation and remorseless murder, there’s nothing this dictator won’t do to fulfil his ambitions.
character_quote: Bow down before my Psycho Power!
character_motive_description: He is a self-imposed dictator and megalomaniac seeking world domination.

character_bio: The adopted son of Heihachi Mishima, raised to be a rival for Kazuya Mishima. After abandoning the Zaibatsu for various reasons, he ended up idling his time away in the Bahamas as manager of his own company… until a certain event disturbed his permanent vacation and entwined his fate with the Zaibatsu once again.
character_quote: Leave it to me. I won't disappoint.
character_motive_description: He is embroiled in a one-sided rivalry with his adoptive brother, Kazuya Mishima.

character_bio: A savage fighter who uses a kickboxing fighting style. He's reported to have died twice and was somehow revived each time. He once belonged to an international police force, but Dr. Abel and Dr. Bosconovitch made him a replicant with a perpetual generator that keeps him alive.
character_quote: Mwahahahaha! So, which one of you wants to die?
character_motive_description: A power-hungry kickboxer, he was once an Interpol officer until he was killed in a shootout and revived by Dr. Abel.

character_bio: Feng Wei had always abided by what was written on the God Fist scroll: 'Defeat all other masters and conquer their styles; the perfect warrior transcends all to become the Dragon God.' Having fought masters of many different styles, Feng returned to his childhood training ground to continue his intense training regime. Then one day, an unexpected visitor appeared before Feng: a mysterious man who exuded strength. When the man made it clear that his desire was to fight, Feng had no reason to refuse. He accepted his opponent's challenge in silence, and prepared to battle.
character_quote: Come on!
character_motive_description: He seeks the secrets of the God Fist scrolls that were stolen by the Mishima family.

character_bio: Making her Street Fighter debut, Menat is the apprentice of a famous fortune-teller. She fights with a crystal sphere that she controls with her soul power.
character_quote: Have you considered your destiny? Do you believe in fate?
character_motive_description: She is the Soul Power wielding apprentice of Rose.

character_bio: First appearing in Street Fighter Alpha 3, Rainbow Mika is a pro wrestler who idolises Zangief. Many of her special moves are exaggerated versions of real-life wrestling techniques.
character_quote: I'll kick your ass! All right! Let's begiiiin!!!
character_motive_description: She is a Japanese professional wrestler from the Iwashigahama Japan Women's Pro-Wrestling organization.

character_bio: First appearing in Street Fighter III: New Generation, Alex is a hard-hitting fighter who combines wrestling and kick-boxing techniques for dramatic effect. He lives in Manhattan and trains with Tom, a friend of his late father.
character_quote: Okay. Let's rumble.
character_motive_description: He enters the third World Warrior tournament after its sponsor, Gill, seriously injures his best friend and father figure Tom.

character_bio: If there’s one character in the Street Fighter universe that can be described as pure evil, it has to be M. Bison. Brainwashing, human experimentation and remorseless murder, there’s nothing this dictator won’t do to fulfil his ambitions.
character_quote: Bow down before my Psycho Power!
character_motive_description: He is a self-imposed dictator and megalomaniac seeking world domination.

character_bio: Once a fighter who had won the hearts of fans with his excellent sensibility and handsome good looks, he decided to transform himself completely by gaining weight to eliminate the perceived disadvantage he had in a fight due to his body type. His fans were disappointed, as on the outside it looked like he'd merely put on a few too many pounds, but Bob was definitely pleased with himself.
character_quote: Speed and weight!
character_motive_description: He entered the sixth tournament to silence his doubters.

character_bio: After he defeated Azazel, Jin Kazama was apprehended by UN troops. As his unconscious body was being transported by helicopter, he became possessed by his devil form, ripped free from his straitjacket, tore through the helicopter's fuselage with a powerful beam attack, and then escaped. Intermittently fending off the UN's attempts to recapture him, Devil Jin wandered the desert until he stumbled across a town in the Middle East. His arrival at the town's bazaar sent the civilians fleeing for their lives, turning the once buzzing settlement into an abandoned husk. That is until a certain someone showed his face…
character_quote: Fear my wrath.
character_motive_description: He seeks to achieve ultimate power and will do whatever it takes to achieve it.

character_bio: Once a mindless doll under the control of Shadaloo, Cammy broke free of her brainwashing and joined a Special Forces unit called Delta Red. Her former codename was Killer Bee. She also has a fondness for cats.
character_quote: I fight for those I want to protect!
character_motive_description: She is an MI6 operative for the British government.

character_bio: Eddy Gordo went to G Corporation to exact revenge on Kazuya Mishima for murdering his father. After he'd taken out a crowd of guards, a young girl in a strange outfit stood before him, and struck a pose. 'You're not getting past me, old man! Teehee!' What did she mean by 'old man'? Confused and irritated by her appearance and disrespectful tone, but aware of the threat she posed, Eddy prepared to fight.
character_quote: Don't think I'll go easy on you.
character_motive_description: His storyline revolves around his quest for revenge for the murder of his parents.

character_bio: Ling Xiaoyu infiltrated the Mishima Zaibatsu building in search of information relating to Jin Kazama's disappearance. Creeping deeper into the enemy territory under the guards' noses, she eventually hears Heihachi Mishima's voice coming from a room; he was giving orders about locating Jin. Just as Xiaoyu was about to sneak into the room, a man dressed all in white emerged and pushed her back. 'Take me to Jin!' Xiaoyu demanded, unflinching. The man stood there for a moment, before ordering Xiaoyu to follow him. He led her to the roof, then silently turned toward her, and readied himself to fight. Xiaoyu took up her fighting stance, and said, 'So that's how it is... If you think I'm just some little girl, you're sadly mistaken.'
character_quote: I'm going to stop Jin!
character_motive_description: She is a sixteen-year-old Chinese martial artist.

character_bio: A mysterious fighter… a demon. He finds himself in the middle of the Mishima blood feud by a pre-existing relationship with Kazumi, Hehiachi's wife. He makes his debut in TEKKEN 7 promising to fulfill a debt owed to Kazumi.
character_quote: Can you withstand my power?
character_motive_description: He seeks to repay a debt to Kazumi Mishima for saving his life from an unknown critical situation.

character_quote: Boom! That's how to start a fight and finish it quickly!
character_motive_description: She has a desire to promote her family's fighting style.

character_bio: The Sirius Marksmen, a secret society of exorcists, has exerted a profound influence on European history for hundreds of years. The most powerful exorcist of the current generation is Claudio, who was visiting the Mishima Zaibatsu as their groups join forces to subdue a certain evil. After sharing information on the targets, Kazuya Mishima and Jin Kazama, Claudio left the control room only to be confronted by a young girl. He was about to call the guards when she demanded to be taken to Jin. A plan sprung to Claudio's mind. He led her to the roof, and with a grin prepared to face her in combat.
character_quote: This is no place for amateurs.
character_motive_description: He is a leader of a secret Anti-Devil organization in combating the Devil Gene's threat.

character_quote: Come on, let's turn up the heat.
character_motive_description: His goal is to test his power against many different fighters and strives to become stronger.
feedback: None were difficult to answer and everything made sense. Interesting study.

character_bio: Katarina Alves lost both her parents at a young age, and spent several years at an orphanage before being adopted by a man she'd never met. Initially, Katarina rebelled against him using a whole manner of profane language, but the man's kindness and patience eventually wore her hard exterior down. In time, they grew close, though her penchant for profane language remained. One day, Katarina's adoptive father vanished. As much as she wanted to find him, she lacked the money to do so. But then she learned of the King of Iron Fist Tournament. The savage techniques the man had taught her gave Katarina hope that she could win and take the cash prize. The day of the first match arrived, and the arena was none other than the roof of G Corporation's Millennium Tower. When Katarina first laid eyes on her opponent, all she saw was an enormous hulk of muscle. There was no way he could be human…
character_quote: Sorry, but you're gonna have to die.
character_motive_description: She is currently searching for her missing adoptive father.

character_bio: After losing his sister in an airstrike ordered by the Mishima Zaibatsu under the direction of Jin Kazama, Miguel Caballero Rojo devoted his life to seeking revenge. However, when Jin suddenly vanishes without a trace, Miguel's life purpose disappears along with him. From that point forward, Miguel began to wander like a specter from battle-torn town to battle-torn town. One day, as he ambled through rows of dilapidated buildings, he stumbled across a strangely familiar hooded man. There in front of him was none other than his sworn enemy, Jin. Consumed by both euphoria and rage, Miguel becomes frenzied and goes in for the kill.
character_quote: You look like you're ready to lose.
character_motive_description: He fights to avenge his sister who is killed on her wedding day by Mishima Zaibatsu fighter jets.

character_bio: As the first lady of Street Fighter, Chun-Li is widely regarded as the strongest woman in the world. She’s an agent for Interpol and is hell-bent on bringing both M. Bison and Shadaloo to justice.
character_quote: I'll show you my Kung-Fu!
character_motive_description: She relentlessly seeks revenge for the death of her father at the hands of M. Bison.

character_quote: Power is everything.
character_motive_description: He wishes to avenge the apparent death of his mother Jun Kazama.

One day, while she was out running on her usual training course along the mountain roads, she was suddenly confronted by an enormous, hairy creature! Josie screamed, and then fled half in tears, but the creature remained hot on her heels. Realizing she had little chance of escape, Josie abruptly came to a halt, then turned trembling, to face her feral foe…
character_quote: I got this!
character_motive_description: She reluctantly agrees to her parents expectations and train Kickboxing.

character_motive_description: He is a major in the United States Air Force whose goal is to finish the criminal organization Shadaloo.

character_quote: I'll show you my Kung-Fu!
character_motive_description: She relentlessly seeks revenge for the death of her father at the hands of M. Bison.

character_bio: Kazuya was raised as the heir to the Mishima Zaibatsu, but rebelled against his father Heihachi. After awakening the power of the devil within him, he's finally able to control it.
character_quote: It's time for you to meet your end!
character_motive_description: He seeks to take revenge against his father for having thrown him down a cliff years prior.

character_bio: Feng Wei had always abided by what was written on the God Fist scroll: 'Defeat all other masters and conquer their styles; the perfect warrior transcends all to become the Dragon God.' Having fought masters of many different styles, Feng returned to his childhood training ground to continue his intense training regime. Then one day, an unexpected visitor appeared before Feng: a mysterious man who exuded strength. When the man made it clear that his desire was to fight, Feng had no reason to refuse. He accepted his opponent's challenge in silence, and prepared to battle.
character_quote: Come on!
character_motive_description: He seeks the secrets of the God Fist scrolls that were stolen by the Mishima family.

character_bio: Heir to the Masters family fortune, Ken is a flamoyant fighter who learned the art of Ansatsuken from Gouken. He also grew up alongside Ryu, a man he considers both his best friend and ultimate rival.
character_quote: Come on, let's turn up the heat.
character_motive_description: His goal is to test his power against many different fighters and strives to become stronger.

character_bio: A mysterious fighter… a demon. He finds himself in the middle of the Mishima blood feud by a pre-existing relationship with Kazumi, Hehiachi's wife. He makes his debut in TEKKEN 7 promising to fulfill a debt owed to Kazumi.
character_quote: Can you withstand my power?
character_motive_description: He seeks to repay a debt to Kazumi Mishima for saving his life from an unknown critical situation.

character_bio: Written off as dead after the events of the Street Fighter Alpha series, Nash makes an unexpected return in Street Fighter V. His Frankenstein’s monster-esque appearance suggests he’s not the harbinger of justice we once knew…
character_quote: I'll show no mercy!
character_motive_description: He is a former Captain of the United States Air Force and friend of Guile.

character_bio: First appearing in Street Fighter III: New Generation, Alex is a hard-hitting fighter who combines wrestling and kick-boxing techniques for dramatic effect. He lives in Manhattan and trains with Tom, a friend of his late father.
character_quote: Okay. Let's rumble.
character_motive_description: He enters the third World Warrior tournament after its sponsor, Gill, seriously injures his best friend and father figure Tom.

character_bio: First appearing in Super Street Fighter II Turbo as a secret boss, Akuma remains one of the most powerful characters in the Street Fighter universe. Unlike Ryu and Ken, he embraces the killing intent of the Satsu no Hado.
character_quote: Hmph. So it's you…
character_motive_description: He is an emotionless and powerful warrior fixated on mastering the Satsui no Hado.

character_bio: Standing eight feet tall, Abigail is the tallest character in Street Fighter history. He's a former boss of the Mad Gear gang, and has a fanatical obsession with cars.
character_quote: Vroom! Vroom! Vroom! Rrrrt! Ha ha ha!
character_motive_description: He supposedly renounced his life of crime and started a mechanic's garage.

character_bio: Kazumi Mishima, wife of Heihachi Mishima, is well versed in Hachijyo Karate. She was childhood friends with her husband Heihachi and eventually they fell in love. Through their love they birthed a healthy young boy. Fast forward a few years later, Heihachi would become the head of a huge organization called the Mishima Zaibatsu, with plans to conquer the world. Kazumi loved Heihachi unconditionally, but at the same time he was beginning to feel dangerous. In this state, Heihachi threw the world into a war and Kazumi took it upon herself to stop him.
character_quote: I will teach you the meaning of fear.
character_motive_description: She married to Heihachi because her clan foresaw his attempted world domination in the future and sent her to kill him.

character_bio: A former officer of the Mishima Zaibatsu's special military unit, the Tekken Force, Lars enacted a coup d'état and rebelled against his former employer. Lars continues to fight despite the loss of his fallen comrades, and his bloody rebellion is nowhere near finished.
character_quote: Think you can stop me?
character_motive_description: He is a member of the Tekken Force paramilitary unit, confronting the corrupt Mishima Zaibatsu corporation.
ethnicity_description: I Am Half German And Half English. I Just Consider Myself To Be Anglo/Saxon Or Just White.
feedback: Nothing that comes to mind at this present moment.

feedback: Nothing that comes to mind at this present moment.

character_bio: By travelling the world to improve his fighting ability, Ryu is the embodiment of the world warrior spirit. He's been the poster boy of the Street Fighter series since its inception.
character_quote: This is the path of destiny!
character_motive_description: He is an experienced martial artist, highly focused on his training, aiming to become the strongest he can.
ethnicity_description: I Am Half German And Half English. I Just Consider Myself To Be Anglo/Saxon Or Just White.
feedback: Nothing that comes to mind at this present moment.

character_bio: If there’s one character in the Street Fighter universe that can be described as pure evil, it has to be M. Bison. Brainwashing, human experimentation and remorseless murder, there’s nothing this dictator won’t do to fulfil his ambitions.
character_quote: Bow down before my Psycho Power!
character_motive_description: He is a self-imposed dictator and megalomaniac seeking world domination.
ethnicity_description: I Am Half German And Half English. I Just Consider Myself To Be Anglo/Saxon Or Just White.
feedback: Nothing that comes to mind at this present moment.

character_bio: It was no secret that G Corporation was locked in a power struggle with the Mishima Zaibatsu. However, within G Corp itself, another battle was raging: the battle to create the ultimate next-gen humanoid weapon. On one side was the development team behind the Jack series led by Jane; on the other was the research team responsible for Gigas, a bio-enhanced super human. With his massive size and uncanny mobility, Gigas was hailed for his versatility in combat, and some saw him as more than capable of dislodging the Jack series from its position as G Corp's premier weapon. Both teams entered their weapons into the King of Iron Fist Tournament to decide once and for all which was the best.
character_motive_description: The various Jack models were originally created by the Mishima Zaibatsu and G Corporation for different purposes.
ethnicity_description: I Am Half German And Half English. I Just Consider Myself To Be Anglo/Saxon Or Just White.
feedback: Nothing that comes to mind at this present moment.

character_bio: Rounding off the quartet of new combatants in Street Fighter V is F.A.N.G. This assassin works for Shadaloo as M. Bison’s second in command.
character_quote: Two minutes! I'll finish you in two minutes!
character_motive_description: He is the second-in-command of Shadaloo, ranking only below M. Bison in the hierarchy.

character_bio: After losing his sister in an airstrike ordered by the Mishima Zaibatsu under the direction of Jin Kazama, Miguel Caballero Rojo devoted his life to seeking revenge. However, when Jin suddenly vanishes without a trace, Miguel's life purpose disappears along with him. From that point forward, Miguel began to wander like a specter from battle-torn town to battle-torn town. One day, as he ambled through rows of dilapidated buildings, he stumbled across a strangely familiar hooded man. There in front of him was none other than his sworn enemy, Jin. Consumed by both euphoria and rage, Miguel becomes frenzied and goes in for the kill.
character_quote: You look like you're ready to lose.
character_motive_description: He fights to avenge his sister who is killed on her wedding day by Mishima Zaibatsu fighter jets.

character_bio: First appearing in Super Street Fighter II Turbo as a secret boss, Akuma remains one of the most powerful characters in the Street Fighter universe. Unlike Ryu and Ken, he embraces the killing intent of the Satsu no Hado.
character_quote: Hmph. So it's you…
character_motive_description: He is an emotionless and powerful warrior fixated on mastering the Satsui no Hado.

character_bio: First appearing in Street Fighter III as a non-playable character, Kolin is a member of the secret Illuminati organization. Gill gifted her the power of ice and she's been loyal to him ever since.
character_quote: It's so nice to meet.
character_motive_description: She is a conniving and devoted agent of the Illuminati.

character_bio: By travelling the world to improve his fighting ability, Ryu is the embodiment of the world warrior spirit. He's been the poster boy of the Street Fighter series since its inception.
character_quote: This is the path of destiny!
character_motive_description: He is an experienced martial artist, highly focused on his training, aiming to become the strongest he can.

character_bio: Daughter of the Kazama Traditional Martial Arts School and known as 'Gang Mediator' in her hometown. Ever since she involved herself in a certain street fight, Lili has viewed her as a rival. She knows that Jin Kazama is her cousin and vows to take him down.
character_quote: When you resort to fighting, everyone loses.
character_motive_description: She believes very strongly in justice and devotes much of her free time to being a "pacifist" vigilante who is breaking up fights.
ethnicity_description: Caucasian (Irish, Scottish, English, French), Native American
normalized_ethnicity: Native American + White + Irish + Scottish + English + French

character_bio: The original leader of the Mishima Zaibatsu, and the fighter known as the 'King of the Iron Fist.' Heihachi continues to fight for control of the Mishima Zaibatsu against his son, Kazuya, and his grandson, Jin. After having recovered from the injuries he sustained in the suicide attack on him from the G Corporation's Jack units, Heihachi is back with an iron fist--and body to match.
character_quote: You fool! I am invincible!
character_motive_description: He is the leader of an empire known as the Mishima Zaibatsu.

character_bio: Last seen in Balrog's ending in Super Street Fighter IV, Ed is a fleet-footed boxer who is infused with psycho power. His body ages faster than normal due to the modifications he received at the hands of S.I.N.
character_quote: Well ain't you a high def picture of strength. I'm shakin' here.
character_motive_description: He is the protégé of Balrog, a potential substitute body for M. Bison.
ethnicity_description: Caucasian (Irish, Scottish, English, French), Native American
normalized_ethnicity: Native American + White + Irish + Scottish + English + French

character_bio: As an agent for the UN's intelligence bureau, Master Raven embarked on her latest top-secret mission: Infiltrate the King of Iron Fist Tournament and confront her assigned target. In the frozen area that was to be her battleground, Master Raven stood, arms folded, face to face with her subordinate's sworn enemy, who simply narrowed his eyes and took up a fighting pose.
character_quote: It's just business. Don't take it personally.
character_motive_description: She is an agent for the UN's intelligence bureau.

character_bio: As one of the two most outlandish characters introduced in Street Fighter II, Dhalsim is a yoga master who can breathe fire and stretch his limbs at will. He’s always been one of the series’ more senior characters, as evidenced by his new white beard.
character_quote: I am not very fond of conflict.
character_motive_description: He enters the tournament to raise money for his village, and continues to roam the world helping those in need.

character_bio: First appearing in Street Fighter III: New Generation, Alex is a hard-hitting fighter who combines wrestling and kick-boxing techniques for dramatic effect. He lives in Manhattan and trains with Tom, a friend of his late father.
character_quote: Okay. Let's rumble.
character_motive_description: He enters the third World Warrior tournament after its sponsor, Gill, seriously injures his best friend and father figure Tom.

character_bio: Eddy Gordo went to G Corporation to exact revenge on Kazuya Mishima for murdering his father. After he'd taken out a crowd of guards, a young girl in a strange outfit stood before him, and struck a pose. 'You're not getting past me, old man! Teehee!' What did she mean by 'old man'? Confused and irritated by her appearance and disrespectful tone, but aware of the threat she posed, Eddy prepared to fight.
character_quote: Don't think I'll go easy on you.
character_motive_description: His storyline revolves around his quest for revenge for the murder of his parents.

character_bio: As one of the four kings of Shadaloo, Balrog is a remorseless boxer who loves money, women, and bourbon. As long as Shadaloo continue to provide him with all three, he will fight for them.
character_quote: There's no escape!
character_motive_description: He is a greedy American boxer and personal bodyguard to M. Bison.

character_bio: As one of the four new characters introduced in Street Fighter V, much of Necalli’s past is shrouded in mystery. His fighting style is best described as animalistic, due to his feral slashes and stomps.
character_quote: Devour-our-our…
character_motive_description: He is an ancient, mysterious entity searching for souls of powerful fighters to devour.

character_bio: Hwoarang sees one man as his rival: Jin Kazama. Jin, CEO of the Mishima Zaibatsu, declared war against the world, and in the ensuing turmoil vanished suddenly, without a trace. Suspecting there is more to Jin's disappearance than meets the eye, Hwoarang vowed to track him down. With only a shred of reliable information at hand, he headed to the Middle East. After a series of dead leads, Hwoarang heard word that a demon had appeared in a town. Without a second thought, he got on his motorcycle and hammered down there. When he arrived, the place had been deserted, save for Jin Kazama in his devil form.
character_quote: Come at me! I'll take you down.
character_motive_description: He is the Taekwondo student of Baek Doo San, and entered the third Tournament to get revenge for his master.

character_bio: Lucky Chloe is a pop sensation, and the face of the G Corporation brand. When a mysterious man burst into G Corp and took out guard after guard with dance-like techniques, Lucky Chloe fearlessly walked right up to him and blocked his path. She threw the man one of her trademark smiles and issued him a challenge: Fight her, and if he loses he'll have to work as her backup dancer! Without caring if he'd accepted the conditions or not, she prepared for battle.
character_quote: Are you ready?
character_motive_description: She is hired by G Corporation to be a mascot commercial

character_bio: The adopted son of Heihachi Mishima, raised to be a rival for Kazuya Mishima. After abandoning the Zaibatsu for various reasons, he ended up idling his time away in the Bahamas as manager of his own company… until a certain event disturbed his permanent vacation and entwined his fate with the Zaibatsu once again.
character_quote: Leave it to me. I won't disappoint.
character_motive_description: He is embroiled in a one-sided rivalry with his adoptive brother, Kazuya Mishima.

character_bio: Known as the Red Cyclone in his native Russia, Zangief is a living mountain of muscle who wrestles bears for fun. He first appeared in Street Fighter II with his signature spinning pile driver.
character_quote: My iron body is invincible! So beware!
character_motive_description: He is a national Russian hero who is always seen fighting for the glory of his country.

character_bio: After he defeated Azazel, Jin Kazama was apprehended by UN troops. As his unconscious body was being transported by helicopter, he became possessed by his devil form, ripped free from his straitjacket, tore through the helicopter's fuselage with a powerful beam attack, and then escaped. Intermittently fending off the UN's attempts to recapture him, Devil Jin wandered the desert until he stumbled across a town in the Middle East. His arrival at the town's bazaar sent the civilians fleeing for their lives, turning the once buzzing settlement into an abandoned husk. That is until a certain someone showed his face…
character_quote: Fear my wrath.
character_motive_description: He seeks to achieve ultimate power and will do whatever it takes to achieve it.

character_bio: Written off as dead after the events of the Street Fighter Alpha series, Nash makes an unexpected return in Street Fighter V. His Frankenstein’s monster-esque appearance suggests he’s not the harbinger of justice we once knew…
character_quote: I'll show no mercy!
character_motive_description: He is a former Captain of the United States Air Force and friend of Guile.

character_bio: Making her Street Fighter debut, Menat is the apprentice of a famous fortune-teller. She fights with a crystal sphere that she controls with her soul power.
character_quote: Have you considered your destiny? Do you believe in fate?
character_motive_description: She is the Soul Power wielding apprentice of Rose.

character_bio: With a history that dates back to the original Street Fighter, Birdie’s appearance has changed dramatically over the years. He’s gone from being a muscular brute in the Alpha series to a beer bellied glutton in Street Fighter V.
character_quote: Oi! It ain't too late to run home to Mum, now!
character_motive_description: He is a hulking black British punk rocker who fights using chains.

character_bio: By travelling the world to improve his fighting ability, Ryu is the embodiment of the world warrior spirit. He's been the poster boy of the Street Fighter series since its inception.
character_quote: This is the path of destiny!
character_motive_description: He is an experienced martial artist, highly focused on his training, aiming to become the strongest he can.

character_bio: As a top contender for the wealthiest fighter in the Street Fighter universe, Karin Kanzuki is understandably snobbish. She also counts the likes of Sakura, Ken and R. Mika among her rivals.
character_quote: I'll show you the divide in our class!
character_motive_description: Her father is a rather strict man as he constantly pushes his daughter into becoming a better heir to the Kanzuki family fortune, as he wanted a son.
feedback: The questions about whether the characters represented their race/gender were a bit vague because I felt I didn't have enough information to accurately make that call. Same with the question about being a good role model, although some characters were easier to decide based on the description

character_bio: Much like Dee Jay before him, Rashid is an enthusiastic fighter who's rarely seen without a smile on his face. He's also something of a gadget lover, as can be seen by the tornado-firing rucksack he carries on his back.
character_quote: I'm Rashid of the turbulent wind. Remember the name well.
character_motive_description: Rashid is travelling the world in search of a missing friend who has been kidnapped by Shadaloo.

character_bio: When Paul Phoenix, the golden boy of the martial arts world, steps into the ring, the excitement in the crowd is palpable. But this time when his opponent's name rang over the arena's loudspeakers, he could only scratch his head in disbelief. It was Kuma… again! However, Kuma was nowhere to be seen. Word went round that the bear had dropped out of the tournament. The ring announcer informed the spectators of a last-minute change to the fight card. Relieved, Paul awaits the entrance of his long-anticipated human opponent…
character_quote: I'll show you the power of the strongest in the universe… but not for free!
character_motive_description: He fights in hopes of winning the prize money and to prove he is the world's best fighter.
